{"type":"message","id":"5d123f81","parentId":"07c28057","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:36:11.509Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Scanning for Secrets**\n\nI've successfully created the `history_dump.txt` file by using `git log`. Now, I need to focus on scanning this file to look for any potential secrets that might be exposed. I'll need to figure out what key patterns to look for.\n\n\n**Prioritizing the Scan**\n\nI've checked the `README.md` and the badge seems okay, so that's done. I'm now drafting a Python script to scan `history_dump.txt` for specific patterns – namely, `8461845004:` and `AIza`. After that, I will review the `ci-cd.yml` file to ensure the configuration is correct and safe, since I wrote it without reviewing earlier.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771169771383_457","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import re\n\ndef scan_file(filepath):\n    patterns = {\n        \"Telegram Token\": r\"8461845004:[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+\",\n        \"Google Key\": r\"AIza[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+\",\n        \"DMarket Public\": r\"dmarket_public_key\", # General search\n        \"DMarket Secret\": r\"dmarket_secret_key\"  # General search\n    }\n    \n    found = False\n    with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8', errors='ignore') as f:\n        for line_num, line in enumerate(f, 1):\n            for name, pattern in patterns.items():\n                if re.search(pattern, line):\n                    print(f\"FOUND {name} at line {line_num}: {line.strip()[:100]}...\")\n                    found = True\n                    \n    if not found:\n        print(\"No secrets found in history.\")\n\nscan_file(\"D:/Dmarket_bot/history_dump.txt\")\n","file_path":"scan_secrets.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":64249,"output":587,"cacheRead":15685,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64836,"cost":{"input":0.128498,"output":0.007044,"cacheRead":0.0031370000